FBIS4-53590 "dreas098_n_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 Vietnam Vietsovpetro `Striving' To Increase Oil Production Vietsovpetro `Striving' To Increase Oil Production BK2005102994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 0500 GMT 20 May 94 BK2005102994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network Vietnamese BFN [Text] The Vietnam Oil and Natural Gas General Corporation's Vietsovpetro joint enterprise is striving to exploit various new oil wells and develop old ones to increase crude oil production. As of 15 May, the enterprise had produced more than 2.5 million tonnes of crude oil. It has also exploited the acid substances produced at the bottom of oil wells and has signed contracts to improve conditions at various oil wells to increase the production output by 8,000 tonnes per day. While making great efforts to improve conditions at new and old oil wells, the enterprise is renovating the oil tanker Ba Vi to assist in the exploitation of oil fields in the third quarter this year.
